body:
## Code
```rust
let mut s = "s".to_string();

let mref = &mut s;
let ref1 = &*mref; // <- reborrow occurs here

// ^ the end of lifetime of `mref` I've thought

let ref2 = &s;
println!("{}, {}", ref1, ref2); 
```
The mutable reference `mref` were not used anymore after reborrowed. But It seems that it's lifetime were not over when I used `ref1`.

## Result
```
error[E0502]: cannot borrow `s` as immutable because it is also borrowed as mutable
   --> tests/borrow.rs:272:16
    |
267 |     let mref = &mut s;
    |                ------ mutable borrow occurs here
...
272 |     let ref2 = &s;
    |                ^^ immutable borrow occurs here
273 |     println!("{}, {}", ref1, ref2);
    |                        ---- mutable borrow later used here
```

##  Other case
```rust
        let mut s = "s".to_string();
        let mref = &mut s;
        let ref1: &String = mref as &String;
        let ref2 = &s;
        println!("{}, {}", ref1, ref2); 
```
